records.addlTxt:
Defendant Justin Ellis in court.  Attorney Imran Kurter in court for Justin Ellis.  Attorney Patrick O'Keefe in court for State of Wisconsin. 
CASE HELD OFF THE RECORD PER JUDGE.  Case in court for status conference.  Defense intends to file a suppression motion.  Court sets a status date.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.
Status conference scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed: Pretrial Services 10-10-2022 Supervision Report

Defendant Justin Ellis appeared by video.  Attorney Imran Kurter appeared by video for Justin Ellis.  Attorney Patrick O'Keefe appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
CASE HELD OFF THE RECORD PER JUDGE.  Case in court for scheduling conference.  Defense requests a status date.  Court set date as requested.  Case adjourned to Branch 40. This case may be heard via Zoom. Zoom meeting information provided to parties.
Status conference scheduled for October 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed: Pretrial Services Supervision Report 9.2.22

Defendant Justin Ellis in court with Attorney Imran Kurter; both appear in person.  Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 40, Judge Shelton. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 40.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed: Pretrial Services Supervision Report 7.12.22

Defendant Justin Ellis in court.  Patrick O'Keefe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for an indigency hearing.  Defendant appears in Court without counsel.  Defendant is not eligible for public defender representation. Defendant requests court appointed counsel at the county rate. Court appoints Attorney Imran Kurter who shall be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. Court orders defendant to repay the County at a rate of $50.00/month beginning upon completion of the case and every month thereafter until paid in full.  Case adjourned for a preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary Hearing scheduled on July 12, 2022 at 8:30 AM.
Received and Filed: Pretrial Services Supervision Report 7.8.22

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Court orders defendant to be monitored by portable breathalyzers. Court ordered SCRAM bracelet to monitor the Defendant maintains absolute sobriety. No driving without a valid license.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Justin Ellis in court with attorney Maryann Corea.  Defendant Justin Ellis in custody.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Justin Ellis appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings. DEFENDANT IS NOT INDIGENT. Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 4, 5, and 6. This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.  Indigency hearing scheduled for July 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
